reviews.review_text: what can els can ya say man? i wont review this show song by song.i mean despite jerys voice problems this hrtfd. run the boys were so on onthis night. jery gave his all and ten some. just shows the love he had for us all. great f;n show. brings back lots of memories from those nights.tiedies hanging off the upper levels the whole way around the place, what happened ?
excellent sound commenting only on the recording...excellent well balanced audience tape.  definately a keeper if you like auds!

Great The energy in this show is intense.  Jerry's voice may be shot, but so what?  After a trippy Other One and an stratospheric Stella Blue, the Good Lovin' would have been a perfectly acceptable ending to a very good show.  But then, they decided to tack on a Dear Mr. Fantasy, and what a version.  It didn't seem possible to top the peak of the Stella, but they seem to have actually pulled it off.
